{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/swift-docc.SwiftDocC\/documentation\/SwiftDocC\/AddingFeatureFlags"],"title":"Development","generated":true,"anchor":"Development"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/swift-docc.SwiftDocC\/documentation\/SwiftDocC\/Features","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Over time as we develop new features in DocC we also add, update, or remove the flags and options that the "},{"code":"docc","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" executable accepts. So that other tools can know what flags and options a certain version of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"docc"},{"text":" executable accepts, we add new entries in the “features.json” file.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Adding-a-New-Feature","text":"Adding a New Feature","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When adding a new collection of command line flags or options to the "},{"code":"docc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" executable that relate to some new feature, add a new entry to the “feature.json” file that name the new feature. For example:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","  \"features\": [","    {","      \"name\": \"name-of-first-feature\"","    },","    {","      \"name\": \"name-of-second-feature\"","    }","  ]","}"]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a single entry for multiple related command line flags and options if they are all added in the same build."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note"},{"anchor":"Checking-what-Features-DocC-Supports","text":"Checking what Features DocC Supports","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In a Swift toolchain, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"docc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" executable is installed at ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"usr\/bin\/docc"},{"type":"text","text":". In the same toolchain, the “features.json” file is installed at "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"usr\/share\/docc\/features.json"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tools that call the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"docc"},{"type":"text","text":" executable from a Swift toolchain can read the “features.json” file to check if a specific feature is available in that build."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The feature entry describes the feature name and doesn’t list what command line flags or options that feature corresponds to."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Add features to DocC and indicate the feature’s availability to other tools."}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftdocc\/features"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"SwiftDocC"}],"title":"Indicating Feature Availability to Tools","roleHeading":"Article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/swift-docc.SwiftDocC\/documentation\/SwiftDocC"]]},"references":{"doc://swift-docc.SwiftDocC/documentation/SwiftDocC":{"role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Combine code comments with markup prose to produce structured, semantic documentation."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/swift-docc.SwiftDocC\/documentation\/SwiftDocC","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftdocc","title":"SwiftDocC"},"doc://swift-docc.SwiftDocC/documentation/SwiftDocC/AddingFeatureFlags":{"kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/swift-docc.SwiftDocC\/documentation\/SwiftDocC\/AddingFeatureFlags","title":"Adding Feature Flags","url":"\/documentation\/swiftdocc\/addingfeatureflags","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Develop experimental features by adding feature flags."}],"type":"topic"}}}